&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;self&lt;/code&gt; refers to the specific object instance created from a class. But why must every method explicitly include &lt;code&gt;self&lt;/code&gt; as a parameter?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-py s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-python&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title class_&quot;&gt;MyClass&lt;/span&gt;:
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;func&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-params&quot;&gt;self, name&lt;/span&gt;):
        self.name = name
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conversely, in Ruby, there is no &lt;code&gt;self&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-rb s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title class_&quot;&gt;MyClass&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;func&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-params&quot;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;)
        &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;@name&lt;/span&gt; = name
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
